# ============================================================
# CURSOR RULES — UI STANDARDS & BUTTON SYSTEM
# ============================================================

# ------------------------------------------------------------
# BUTTONS — CORE RULES (NEVER BREAK THESE)
# ------------------------------------------------------------

BUTTONS:
- ALWAYS use inline-flex + items-center + justify-content: center on every button, no exceptions.
- NEVER use fixed pixel widths (e.g. width: 120px) on buttons. Use padding to control size.
- ALWAYS use padding for sizing, never hardcoded width or height values.
- ALWAYS set a minimum height of 44px and minimum width of 44px for mobile touch targets.
- NEVER hardcode font sizes in pixels. Use rem, em, or Tailwind text classes.
- ALWAYS use white-space: nowrap to prevent button text from wrapping.
- ALWAYS use gap (not margin) to space icons and text inside buttons.
- NEVER use display: block or display: inline on buttons. Always flex.

# ------------------------------------------------------------
# BUTTON SIZES — USE THESE EXACTLY
# ------------------------------------------------------------

BUTTON SIZE CLASSES (Tailwind):
- Small:      inline-flex items-center justify-center px-3 py-1.5 text-sm min-h-[44px]
- Medium:     inline-flex items-center justify-center px-5 py-2.5 text-base min-h-[44px]
- Large:      inline-flex items-center justify-center px-8 py-3.5 text-lg min-h-[44px]
- Full Width: flex items-center justify-center w-full px-5 py-2.5 min-h-[44px]

BUTTON BASE CSS (always apply):
button, .btn {
  display: inline-flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  gap: 0.5rem;
  padding: 0.625rem 1.25rem;
  min-height: 44px;
  min-width: 44px;
  white-space: nowrap;
  overflow: hidden;
  text-overflow: ellipsis;
  font-size: 1rem;
  line-height: 1.5;
  border-radius: 0.375rem;
  cursor: pointer;
  transition: all 0.2s ease;
}

# ------------------------------------------------------------
# TYPOGRAPHY — RULES
# ------------------------------------------------------------

TYPOGRAPHY:
- NEVER use hardcoded pixel font sizes. Use rem, em, or Tailwind text-* classes.
- Body text: text-base (1rem)
- Small/caption: text-sm (0.875rem)
- Heading sizes: text-lg, text-xl, text-2xl, text-3xl, text-4xl only
- Line height: always set leading-normal (1.5) or higher
- ALWAYS ensure sufficient color contrast (min 4.5:1 ratio for normal text)

# ------------------------------------------------------------
# LAYOUT & SPACING — RULES
# ------------------------------------------------------------

LAYOUT:
- ALWAYS use flexbox or CSS grid for layout. Never use float or inline-block for layout.
- ALWAYS use gap for spacing between flex/grid children, not margin between siblings.
- NEVER use arbitrary magic numbers for spacing. Use the Tailwind spacing scale (4, 8, 12, 16, 20, 24, 32, 40, 48, 64px).
- Responsive breakpoints: always design mobile-first, then md:, lg:, xl:.
- Page max-width: max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8

# ------------------------------------------------------------
# COMPONENTS
# ------------------------------------------------------------

COMPONENTS:
- Prefer Shadcn/ui components when available: https://ui.shadcn.com
- Fallback to DaisyUI for rapid Tailwind-based components: https://daisyui.com
- Use Radix UI primitives for accessibility-critical components (modals, dropdowns, tooltips)
- NEVER build modals, dropdowns, or tooltips from scratch — use a library

# ------------------------------------------------------------
# ICONS INSIDE BUTTONS
# ------------------------------------------------------------

ICON BUTTONS:
- ALWAYS wrap icon + label in a flex container with gap-2
- Icon size: h-4 w-4 (small button) or h-5 w-5 (medium/large button)
- NEVER use margin-right on icons. Use gap on the parent.
- Icon-only buttons MUST have an aria-label for accessibility

Example:
<button className="inline-flex items-center justify-center gap-2 px-5 py-2.5 min-h-[44px] text-base">
  <Icon className="h-5 w-5" />
  Button Label
</button>

# ------------------------------------------------------------
# FORMS & INPUTS
# ------------------------------------------------------------

INPUTS:
- ALWAYS match input height to adjacent button height (min 44px)
- ALWAYS use w-full on inputs inside form containers
- NEVER use fixed pixel widths on inputs
- ALWAYS include a visible label (not just placeholder text)
- Base input padding: 0.625rem 0.875rem

# ------------------------------------------------------------
# RESPONSIVENESS
# ------------------------------------------------------------

RESPONSIVE RULES:
- ALWAYS test layouts at 375px (mobile), 768px (tablet), 1280px (desktop)
- NEVER use fixed pixel widths on containers — use %, max-w, or w-full
- Minimum font size for any UI text: text-sm (14px)
- Buttons on mobile must be full-width or min 44px tap target in both dimensions
- Stacking order on mobile: content above buttons, labels above inputs

# ------------------------------------------------------------
# QA CHECKLIST — RUN BEFORE EVERY COMMIT
# ------------------------------------------------------------

BEFORE SHIPPING ANY UI, VERIFY:
[ ] Button text is horizontally AND vertically centered
[ ] No button text wraps to a second line
[ ] All buttons are at least 44px tall
[ ] No hardcoded pixel widths on buttons or inputs
[ ] UI looks correct at 75%, 100%, 125% browser zoom
[ ] Icons and text inside buttons use gap, not margin
[ ] All interactive elements have hover and focus states
[ ] Color contrast passes 4.5:1 minimum ratio
[ ] No layout breaks at 375px mobile width
[ ] Forms have visible labels (not just placeholders)

# ------------------------------------------------------------
# ANTI-PATTERNS — NEVER DO THESE
# ------------------------------------------------------------

NEVER:
- width: 120px on a button
- height: 40px on a button (use min-height + padding instead)
- font-size: 14px (use rem or Tailwind classes)
- margin-right: 8px on an icon inside a button (use gap)
- display: block on a button
- <button><div>Label</div></button> (no block elements inside buttons)
- Placeholder text as the only label for an input field
- Skipping focus/hover states on interactive elements
